altigaPptpStatsMibModule.name: altigaPptpStatsMibModule
altigaPptpStatsMibModule.contactinfo: Cisco Systems 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-cvpn3000@cisco.com
altigaPptpStatsMibModule.description: The Altiga PPTP Statistics MIB models counters and objects that are of management interest for PPTP tunnels. Acronyms The following acronyms are used in this document: MIB: Management Information Base PPTP: Point-to-Point Tunneling Protocol

alPptpStatsLocalProtVers.name: alPptpStatsLocalProtVers
alPptpStatsLocalProtVers.description: This object describes the protocol version and revision of the local implementation. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

alPptpStatsLocalFraming.name: alPptpStatsLocalFraming
alPptpStatsLocalFraming.description: A set of bits indicating the PPTP framing capabilities of this system.

alPptpStatsLocalBearer.name: alPptpStatsLocalBearer
alPptpStatsLocalBearer.description: A set of bits indicating the PPTP bearer capabilities of this system.

alPptpStatsLocalFirmwareRev.name: alPptpStatsLocalFirmwareRev
alPptpStatsLocalFirmwareRev.description: This object defines the local firmware revision.

alPptpStatsTotalTunnels.name: alPptpStatsTotalTunnels
alPptpStatsTotalTunnels.description: This object returns the total number of tunnels, including those that did not reach the established state.

alPptpStatsActiveTunnels.name: alPptpStatsActiveTunnels
alPptpStatsActiveTunnels.description: This object returns the number of tunnels that are currently active.

alPptpStatsMaxTunnels.name: alPptpStatsMaxTunnels
alPptpStatsMaxTunnels.description: The maximum number of simultaneously active PPTP tunnels since the system was booted.

alPptpStatsTotalSessions.name: alPptpStatsTotalSessions
alPptpStatsTotalSessions.description: This object returns the total number of sessions, including those that did not reach the established state.

alPptpStatsActiveSessions.name: alPptpStatsActiveSessions
alPptpStatsActiveSessions.description: This object returns the number of sessions that are currently active.

alPptpStatsMaxSessions.name: alPptpStatsMaxSessions
alPptpStatsMaxSessions.description: The maximum number of simultaneously active PPTP sessions since the system was booted.

alPptpStatsControlRecvOctets.name: alPptpStatsControlRecvOctets
alPptpStatsControlRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets received.

alPptpStatsControlRecvPackets.name: alPptpStatsControlRecvPackets
alPptpStatsControlRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets received.

alPptpStatsControlRecvDiscards.name: alPptpStatsControlRecvDiscards
alPptpStatsControlRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the number of control packets received that were discarded.

alPptpStatsControlSendOctets.name: alPptpStatsControlSendOctets
alPptpStatsControlSendOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints.

alPptpStatsControlSendPackets.name: alPptpStatsControlSendPackets
alPptpStatsControlSendPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints.

alPptpStatsPayloadRecvOctets.name: alPptpStatsPayloadRecvOctets
alPptpStatsPayloadRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were received.

alPptpStatsPayloadRecvPackets.name: alPptpStatsPayloadRecvPackets
alPptpStatsPayloadRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were received.

alPptpStatsPayloadRecvDiscards.name: alPptpStatsPayloadRecvDiscards
alPptpStatsPayloadRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the number of received payload packets that were discarded.

alPptpStatsPayloadSendOctets.name: alPptpStatsPayloadSendOctets
alPptpStatsPayloadSendOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were transmitted to tunnel peers.

alPptpStatsPayloadSendPackets.name: alPptpStatsPayloadSendPackets
alPptpStatsPayloadSendPackets.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were transmitted to tunnel peers.

alPptpStatsTunnelTable.name: alPptpStatsTunnelTable
alPptpStatsTunnelTable.description: The PPTP tunnel status and statistics table.

alPptpStatsTunnelRowStatus.name: alPptpStatsTunnelRowStatus
alPptpStatsTunnelRowStatus.description: The status of this row. Used to terminate the tunnel, cannot be used to create a tunnel.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerIpAddr.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerIpAddr
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerIpAddr.description: The peer's IP address for this tunnel.

alPptpStatsTunnelDatastreamId.name: alPptpStatsTunnelDatastreamId
alPptpStatsTunnelDatastreamId.description: The IP-GRE datastream ID of this tunnel.

alPptpStatsTunnelLocalIpAddr.name: alPptpStatsTunnelLocalIpAddr
alPptpStatsTunnelLocalIpAddr.description: The local IP address for this tunnel.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerHostName.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerHostName
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerHostName.description: The peer's host name, as indicated by the peer in a Start-Control-Connection packet.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerVendorName.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerVendorName
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerVendorName.description: The peer's vendor name, as indicated by the peer in a Start-Control-Connection packet.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerFirmwareRev.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerFirmwareRev
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerFirmwareRev.description: This object contains the tunnel peer's firmware revision number. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerProtVers.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerProtVers
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerProtVers.description: This object describes the protocol version and revision of the tunnel peers implementation. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerFramingCap.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerFramingCap
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerFramingCap.description: This object describes the Framing Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerBearerCap.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerBearerCap
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerBearerCap.description: This object describes the Bearer Capabilities of the tunnel peer. If the tunnel is idle this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected.

alPptpStatsTunnelPeerMaxChan.name: alPptpStatsTunnelPeerMaxChan
alPptpStatsTunnelPeerMaxChan.description: The peer's maximum channels value, as indicated by the peer in a Start-Control-Connection packet.

alPptpStatsTunnelActiveSessions.name: alPptpStatsTunnelActiveSessions
alPptpStatsTunnelActiveSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions for this tunnel.

alPptpStatsSessionTable.name: alPptpStatsSessionTable
alPptpStatsSessionTable.description: List of active sessions within tunnels.

alPptpStatsSessionRowStatus.name: alPptpStatsSessionRowStatus
alPptpStatsSessionRowStatus.description: The status of this row. Used to terminate the session, cannot be used to create a Session.

alPptpStatsSessionDatastreamId.name: alPptpStatsSessionDatastreamId
alPptpStatsSessionDatastreamId.description: The GRE-PPP datastream ID of this tunnel, used as the index for this row.

alPptpStatsSessionLocalCallId.name: alPptpStatsSessionLocalCallId
alPptpStatsSessionLocalCallId.description: The local call ID within the tunnel of the session represented by this row.

alPptpStatsSessionPeerCallId.name: alPptpStatsSessionPeerCallId
alPptpStatsSessionPeerCallId.description: The peer call ID within the tunnel of the session represented by this row.

alPptpStatsSessionUserName.name: alPptpStatsSessionUserName
alPptpStatsSessionUserName.description: This object identifies the peer session name on this interface. This is typically the login name of the remote user. If the user name is unknown to the local tunnel peer then this object will contain a null string.

alPptpStatsSessionSerial.name: alPptpStatsSessionSerial
alPptpStatsSessionSerial.description: The call serial number within the tunnel of the session represented by this row.

alPptpStatsSessionMinimumSpeed.name: alPptpStatsSessionMinimumSpeed
alPptpStatsSessionMinimumSpeed.description: The lowest acceptable line speed (in bits/second) for this session, as indicated in the Call-Request packet.

alPptpStatsSessionMaximumSpeed.name: alPptpStatsSessionMaximumSpeed
alPptpStatsSessionMaximumSpeed.description: The highest acceptable line speed (in bits/second) for this session, as indicated in the Call-Request packet.

alPptpStatsSessionConnectSpeed.name: alPptpStatsSessionConnectSpeed
alPptpStatsSessionConnectSpeed.description: The actual line speed (in bits/second) for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionBearerType.name: alPptpStatsSessionBearerType
alPptpStatsSessionBearerType.description: A value indicating the bearer capability required for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionFramingType.name: alPptpStatsSessionFramingType
alPptpStatsSessionFramingType.description: A value indicating the framing capability required for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionPhysicalChannel.name: alPptpStatsSessionPhysicalChannel
alPptpStatsSessionPhysicalChannel.description: The physical channel number used for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionLocalWindowSize.name: alPptpStatsSessionLocalWindowSize
alPptpStatsSessionLocalWindowSize.description: The number of received data packets this system will buffer for this session, as indicated in the setup packets for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionPeerWindowSize.name: alPptpStatsSessionPeerWindowSize
alPptpStatsSessionPeerWindowSize.description: The number of received data packets the peer will buffer for this session, as indicated in the setup packets for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionLocalPpd.name: alPptpStatsSessionLocalPpd
alPptpStatsSessionLocalPpd.description: A measure of the packet processing delay that might be imposed on data sent to this system, in units of 1/10 seconds.

alPptpStatsSessionPeerPpd.name: alPptpStatsSessionPeerPpd
alPptpStatsSessionPeerPpd.description: A measure of the packet processing delay that might be imposed on data sent to the peer, in units of 1/10 seconds.

alPptpStatsSessionRecvOctets.name: alPptpStatsSessionRecvOctets
alPptpStatsSessionRecvOctets.description: This object returns the total number payload octets received for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionRecvPackets.name: alPptpStatsSessionRecvPackets
alPptpStatsSessionRecvPackets.description: This object returns the total number of payload packets received for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionRecvDiscards.name: alPptpStatsSessionRecvDiscards
alPptpStatsSessionRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the total number of payload packets received that were discarded for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionRecvZLB.name: alPptpStatsSessionRecvZLB
alPptpStatsSessionRecvZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowlegement payload packets received for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionSendOctets.name: alPptpStatsSessionSendOctets
alPptpStatsSessionSendOctets.description: This object returns the total number of payload octets transmitted for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionSendPackets.name: alPptpStatsSessionSendPackets
alPptpStatsSessionSendPackets.description: This object returns the total number of payload packets transmitted for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionSendZLB.name: alPptpStatsSessionSendZLB
alPptpStatsSessionSendZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowledgement packets transmitted for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionAckTimeouts.name: alPptpStatsSessionAckTimeouts
alPptpStatsSessionAckTimeouts.description: This object returns the total number of acknowledgement timeouts seen on payload packets for this session.

alPptpStatsSessionLocalFlowOff.name: alPptpStatsSessionLocalFlowOff
alPptpStatsSessionLocalFlowOff.description: Indicates whether the session is in a locally flowed-off state because the number of outstanding unacknowledged packets received from the peer is equal to the local window size.

alPptpStatsSessionPeerFlowOff.name: alPptpStatsSessionPeerFlowOff
alPptpStatsSessionPeerFlowOff.description: Indicates whether the session peer is in a flowed-off state because the number of outstanding unacknowledged packets sent to the peer is equal to the peer's window size.

alPptpStatsSessionOutOfWindow.name: alPptpStatsSessionOutOfWindow
alPptpStatsSessionOutOfWindow.description: The number of data packets received from the peer which were received outside of the offered receive window.

alPptpStatsSessionOutOfSequence.name: alPptpStatsSessionOutOfSequence
alPptpStatsSessionOutOfSequence.description: The number of data packets that were not received in the correct order (as per the sequence number).

alPptpStatsSessionTunnelPeerIpAddr.name: alPptpStatsSessionTunnelPeerIpAddr
alPptpStatsSessionTunnelPeerIpAddr.description: The peer's IP address for the tunnel over which this session is established.

altigaPptpStatsMibCompliance.name: altigaPptpStatsMibCompliance
altigaPptpStatsMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents which implement the Altiga PPTP Statistics MIB.
